       	<body n="f1f0f0"><!-- Change; this is the color of the MS page; value can be any color -->
			<div rend="brown"><!-- Change; this is the color of the writing; only use auto-suggested values -->

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change and repeat as necessary. Always indent <pb>, as here. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><settlement>Philipton</settlement>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><date when="1850-05-23">May 23. <hi rend="underline">1850</hi></date></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup dotted-underline">r</hi> Freeman</persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Owing to the detentions of
<lb/>the past by the rains<!-- rains MBT --> and my absence into
<lb/><region>Caffreland</region> for the recovery of <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Read</persName>,
<lb/>and one of our <choice><sic>childrens</sic><corr>children's</corr></choice> healths I could
<lb/>not reply to yours of the <date when="1850-05-04">4 ultimo</date> till now.</p> <!-- is 4 ultimo May or April 4th? HB --><!-- I'm not sure MBT --><!-- May. AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">1<supplied>.</supplied> I shall take the earliest opportunity of communicating <!-- Not sure how we want to code this list? HB --><!-- I think it's ok as is. MBT -->
<lb/>with <persName>M<hi rend="sup dotted-underline">r</hi> Ulbrecht</persName> about his son.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">2. I have not had any recent information
<lb/>about <region><choice><sic><persName>Madoor</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>Madoor</persName>'s</corr></choice> country</region> - however I <choice><sic>dont</sic><corr>don't</corr></choice> hear
<lb/>a word now about the <unclear>task</unclear> - On <persName>Campbell</persName>
<lb/>shaking his <unclear>tardant</unclear> over <persName>Sir H</persName> by the<!-- Whole line is unclear to me, to be honest! HB --><!-- There's a reference to Lin IL on page 2. maybe "shake his tardant at Lin IL by the" MBT --><!-- This is Sir Harry Smith, governor of the Cape Colony (thanks to Jared for info). AW -->
<lb/>publication of your letter may for

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>the present <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="illegible"/></unclear> farther proceedings &#8211;
<lb/>I met <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Calderwood</persName> <date when="1850-05-22">yesterday</date> &amp; he
<lb/>told me that the <term type="collective"><choice><orig>Boors</orig><reg>Boers</reg></choice></term> have been causing <!-- My instinct is this is Boers, but totes doesn't look like it so I am at a loss! HB --><!-- Boers is my instinct too, but agreed. Maybe also Baans? MBT --><!-- This is Boors, the c19 spelling of Boers (thanks Jared for info). AW -->
<lb/>a disturbance among the <term type="collective">Tambookies</term><!-- orgName? MBT -->, <add place="inline"><seg rend="small">that</seg> <add place="below">is</add></add><!-- that is? MBT -->
<lb/>they have threatened to drive them out
<lb/>of their country &amp; that <del>Govt</del><!-- length word? --> he had advised
<lb/>the Govt<!-- Looks like faut? MBT --> to send a force to apprehend
<lb/>the <del><gap extent="1" unit="chars" agent="illegible"/></del><add place="over-text">r</add>ingleaders among the <term type="collective"><choice><orig>Boors</orig><reg>Boers</reg></choice></term> - but
<lb/>that <persName>Sir H</persName> shrinks from it - It is to be
<lb/>borne<!-- bourne MBT --> in mind that <hi rend="underline">He</hi> first promised
<lb/>the <term type="collective"><choice><orig>Boors</orig><reg>Boers</reg></choice></term> that he would parcel out
<lb/><region>Tambooland</region><!-- I think this is the region mentioned earlier MBT --><!-- Land of the Tam, who are indeed mentioned ealier (thanks, Jared). AW --> among them - I think
<lb/><persName>Sir A</persName><!-- From Jared: Sir Andries Stockenstrom, former Lieutenant Governor of British Kaffraria and an important ally of the evangelical-humanitarian cause in the Cape Colony. AW --> spoke about it to you.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">3. "<unclear>How</unclear><!-- I have aue? MBT --> are you likely to be offended by the
<lb/>constitution <del>"</del>&#8211;?" If justice is done there &amp; is if
<lb/>all who have property to the amount of 50 Â£ <!-- The pound sign he draws has an extra line through the center - how to notate? HB -->
<lb/>be fit for <choice><sic>electons</sic><corr>elections</corr></choice> then will be nearly 7 or <del>7</del><add place="over-text">8</add>00 be <!-- Again, this whole line is a bit murky for me... HB --><!-- be fit for elections then will be newly 7 or 8ao be? MBT --><!-- Fixed with help from Jared. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>have the right of electing as nearly all the
<lb/>erfs are valued by the <orgName>Road Board</orgName><!-- Road Board? Also organization? MBT --> at
<lb/>from 50 to 70 Â£ &#8211; <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>The diagram should
<lb/>be issued immediately as their ostensible reason
<lb/>for not building good houses is for
<lb/>want<!-- I read this as want too. MBT--> of that &amp; the <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">want of</add> security &amp; sense of security
<lb/>of life and property - The <term type="collective">Natives</term> look on
<lb/>the present peace as a hushed volcano = <add place="inline" rend="small">therefore</add>
<lb/>they are disinclined to build at least for the
<lb/>present -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">4. The holder of <region>lands at Kat River</region> may sell
<lb/>and transfer their lands - &amp; therefore it is very
<lb/>likely in a short the lands may fall into the
<lb/>hands of others &#8212;</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">5<supplied>.</supplied> The only thing that can put off this is that the
<lb/><orgName><term type="collective">English</term> Protection Society</orgName> buy up all <hi rend="underline">vacant</hi>
<lb/>erfs &amp; sell them again to other industrious
<lb/><term type="collective">Natives</term> - <del>This</del> There is no risk in such

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>a plan. The old <orgName><term type="collective">English</term> <choice><sic>anti-slavery</sic><corr>Anti-slavery</corr></choice></orgName> &amp;
<lb/><orgName>Protection Societies</orgName> must not abandon
<lb/>the <term type="collective">Natives</term> &#8212;</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">6. I am <del>not</del> of opinion that the <term type="collective">Natives</term> will
<lb/>suffer greatly from the Establishment of a
<lb/>representative assembly - but more from a
<lb/>federal union -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">7 I shall write to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="illegible"/></unclear></persName> by next
<lb/>post about the accounts -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I <choice><sic>intent</sic><corr>intend</corr></choice> this merely as an outline of my
<lb/>views - but I shall <choice><sic>write</sic><corr></corr></choice> deliberately write in
<lb/>the <unclear>conjunction</unclear> with my <unclear>father</unclear> &amp; drink<!-- drink mbt -->
<lb/>to the <orgName>Mission Bloomfield</orgName> <gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="illegible"/> &#8212;</p> <!-- Yikes, this line! HB --><!-- mission Bloanfuld thaut? MBT --><!-- As good as guess as any. AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Be so kind my dear Sir as to present
<lb/>my kindest regards to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Freeman</persName>
<lb/>&amp; your excellent daughters &amp; believe me</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Yours respectfully &amp; affectionately</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><hi rend="underline"><persName>James Read</persName></hi></p>
        
			</div>
